# Agent contract — {{ project_name }}

`README.md` is the human entry point; this file is the agent contract.

## Hard rules

| Never | Instead |
| --- | --- |
| `# type: ignore` / `# noqa` to dodge a finding | fix the root cause |
| lower `coverage_floor` to pass | add tests{% if enable_policy_tests %}; the policy test blocks a silent drop{% endif %} |
| `git commit --no-verify` | make the gate pass |
| weaken a test to make it green | fix the code under test |

## Start here

```bash
uv sync            # install deps + dev group
just               # list recipes
just ci            # the complete gate — must be green before pushing
```

## The gate

`just ci` is the COMPLETE fast gate: fmt-check, lint, typecheck, test+coverage{% if enable_property_tests %}, fuzz{% endif %}{% if enable_policy_tests %}, policy{% endif %}{% if enable_dependency_audit %}, audit{% endif %}.{% if enable_mutation_tests or enable_scanners %} Out-of-band:{% if enable_mutation_tests %} `just mutate` (mutation, non-gating){% endif %}{% if enable_scanners %} `just scan` (semgrep + gitleaks){% endif %}.{% endif %}

## Add a behavior test

Put it in `tests/unit/`. Test the contract, not internals; keep it deterministic. Copy `tests/unit/test_example.py`.
{% if enable_property_tests %}
## Add a property test

Put it in `tests/property/`. It MUST set `pytestmark = pytest.mark.property` and use `@given`. Runs via `just fuzz`. Copy `tests/property/test_example_property.py`.
{% endif %}{% if enable_mutation_tests %}
## Mutation coverage

`just mutate`, then read survivors from `mutants/mutmut-cicd-stats.json`; kill them with `tests/unit/` cases. Non-gating by default.
{% endif %}
## Lint and types

`just lint` / `just fmt` / `just typecheck`. Never inline-dodge a real finding.

## Dependencies

`uv add <pkg>` (runtime) or `uv add --dev <pkg>` (tooling). `uv.lock` is committed; CI runs `uv sync --locked`.
{% if enable_policy_tests %}
## Meta-guardrail

Changing a gate (coverage floor, ruff select, type mode{% if enable_sha_pin_policy %}, Action pins{% endif %}) requires editing the matching test in `tests/policy/` in the SAME commit.
{% endif -%}
